<div id="review_1593215851" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1593215851" />
    <a title="Chitra *CJ*" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46841583-chitra-cj"><img alt="Chitra *CJ*" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479390580p2/46841583.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1593215851?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chitra *CJ*" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chitra *CJ*" href="/user/show/46841583-chitra-cj">Chitra *CJ*</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=heartbreaking">heartbreaking</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=heroines-i-love">heroines-i-love</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=v-card">v-card</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=tearjerker">tearjerker</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=safety-first">safety-first</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=book-husbands">book-husbands</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46841583-chitra-cj?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1593215851" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12623717203048005347">Now my review is going to be biased, as I love JMN and it&apos;s because of her I fell in love with romance.. and &quot;Perfect&quot; was just perfection.<br/><br/>I absolutely love backstories which establish how the characters were molded, and this book has a great introduction to both Zack and Julie.<br/>Zack was born into a privileged family, when a disgruntled grandmother disowns him due to his resemblance to her cheating grandfather. He works hard to become a successful movie actor and director, when one day he finds h</span>
  <span id="freeText12623717203048005347" style="display:none">Now my review is going to be biased, as I love JMN and it's because of her I fell in love with romance.. and "Perfect" was just perfection.<br /><br />I absolutely love backstories which establish how the characters were molded, and this book has a great introduction to both Zack and Julie.<br />Zack was born into a privileged family, when a disgruntled grandmother disowns him due to his resemblance to her cheating grandfather. He works hard to become a successful movie actor and director, when one day he finds his wife cheating on him. Words are spoken in anger and when the next day, Rachel is murdered during a sequence gone wrong, the blame lands on Zach and he's imprisoned.<br />Julie, on the other hand grew up in foster homes, moved from place to place because of her ignored intelligence and thirst to save and help every kid- until she lands in the Mathison family via adoption. From their her life takes a turn and she dedicates herself to becoming a model citizen, daughter, teacher and local Robin Hood. <br />When Zach decides to escape his captivity, he comes across the kind stranger Julie, who decides to help him out but instead ends up kidnapping her.<br />Initially Julie keeps trying to escape, but soon hints of his innocence keep blinding her leading her to doubt herself, ultimately leading to one of my favorite scenes when an escaping Julie runs back to Zach, when he decides to give up and die thinking she has been killed.<br />I absolutely love the contrast between the characters. A sweet and generous Julie falling for a hardened despaired Zach, in a love story which will totally keep you reaching for tissues. Zach was abandoned by his family, humiliated in his trail, dehumanized during his prison stay- while Julie has gone through a lot as a kid until she decides to become a model citizen for her adoptive family- the dilemma both face of staying together in those circumstances is heart warming and pretty well written.<br />I adored their moments in the cabin. From their first lovemaking, to the slow chemistry that blooms; from their happy moments to them discovering each other's pasts- was amazing.<br />A noteworthy mention to certain scenes <br />- Them watching movies in the cabin and him critiquing everything<br />- The morning after the horrible night with the love confession<br />- The press conference post escape <br />- Zack's letter<br />- Julie's confrontation with his grandmother <br />- The betrayal <br />- The aftermath after the truth is exposed<br />- The reconciliation along with the support of family and town<br />The book is full of angst and heart wrenching scenes which are amazingly well written.<br />The secondary characters are very enjoyable, especially Matt, Ted, Carl, Katherine. Matt and Meredith, the characters from Paradise make a HEA appearance.<br />In the end, all the loose ends are tied together and we get a wonderfully amazing HEA.<br />Perfection<br /><br />Safe with exceptions <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ in events following the betrayal, she goes out with Paul (nothing happens, no kissing) and he kisses Diane in anger (again nothing else happens)  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br />5/5</span>
  <a data-text-id="12623717203048005347" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


